    Class Descriptions ğŸ—ï¸
        1ï¸âƒ£ Vehicle (Abstract Class)
            Base class for all vehicles.
            Contains common attributes like ownerName, brand, model, year, color, and countryOfManufacture.
            Defines an abstract method displayInfo(), which must be implemented by subclasses.
        2ï¸âƒ£ Car (Extends Vehicle)
            Includes seat capacity and number of doors.
            Overrides displayInfo() to show car-specific details.
        3ï¸âƒ£ Motorcycle (Extends Vehicle)
            Adds attributes like engine capacity and gear count.
            Overrides displayInfo() to show motorcycle-specific details.
        4ï¸âƒ£ Truck (Extends Vehicle)
            Adds load capacity to represent trucks.
            Overrides displayInfo() to show truck-specific details.
        5ï¸âƒ£ Garage (Manager Class)
        Uses an ArrayList to store vehicles.
            Implements:
                addVehicle()
                updateVehicle()
                removeVehicle()
                displayAllVehicles()
                displayVehicleDetails()
        6ï¸âƒ£ GarageTest (Main Class)
            Provides a menu-driven system using a Scanner for user input.
            Allows users to perform actions like adding, updating, removing, and displaying vehicles.
    Enhancements & Best Practices âœ…
        âœ”ï¸ Final Attributes: year and countryOfManufacture are final since they don't change after creation.
        âœ”ï¸ Encapsulation: Private attributes with public getters/setters ensure data protection.
        âœ”ï¸ Polymorphism: displayInfo() is overridden for different vehicle types.
        âœ”ï¸ Data Validation: Improved input validation in GarageTest.java.
        âœ”ï¸ Iterator for Removal: Uses an Iterator in removeVehicle() to prevent ConcurrentModificationException.
